race.description: Big Event Picnic Tables Maiden Plate
race.comment: THANKS GORGEOUS (11) fought on gamely after doing a lot of early work and finished fourth as the favourite at Sandown-Lakeside. She was fourth again before that in G3 Company at Caulfield, and gets another chance, this time over 1000m, to break her maiden status. SHAPENAPIT (9) settled back from a wide gate at Cranbourne nearly a fortnight ago, and only got going when the race was all over. She gets a nice swing in her draw here, and she will be hard to hold out. LADY OF SOUL (7) battled away well enough on a heavy track in her only start as a juvenile, and is resuming from a spell with a close-up finish at a recent jumpout under her belt. She has the pole position, and she has top 3 claims. WAGGISH (12) makes her debut from a top local stable. Respect the market.
